🧪 Lab Exercise

Create a script named system-info.sh that prints:

Current User
Hostname
Current Date
Current Directory
Linux Kernel Version
Uptime
Memory Usage
Disk Usage

Example:

#!/bin/bash

echo "User : $(whoami)"

echo "Hostname : $(hostname)"

echo "Date : $(date)"

echo "Directory : $(pwd)"

echo "Kernel : $(uname -r)"

echo "Uptime"

uptime

echo "Memory"

free -h

echo "Disk"

df -h
🎯 Senior DevOps Challenge

Create a script named server-health.sh that:

Displays:
Hostname
IP Address
Uptime
CPU Usage
Memory Usage
Disk Usage
Saves the report to server-health-report.txt.
Prints a warning if any filesystem exceeds 80% usage.
Returns exit code 1 if any filesystem exceeds 90% usage.

This is similar to the kind of health check scripts used in production environments.

